    <section id="id1164853772667">
      <title>Ammonolysis</title>
      <para id="id1164853760784">Ammonolysis with ammonia is an analogous reaction to hydrolysis with water, i.e., a dissociation reaction of the ammonia molecule producing H<sup>+</sup> and an NH<sub>2</sub><sup>-</sup> species. Ammonolysis reactions occur with inorganic halides, <link target-id="eip-44454"/> and <link target-id="eip-44455"/>, and organometallic compounds, <link target-id="eip-44456"/>. In both case the NH<sub>2</sub><sup>-</sup> moiety forms a substituent or ligand. </para>




